Fresh Pi session: INDEPENDENTLY VERIFY RED.

Inputs:
- Selected scenario: latest {{run.dir}}/tdd/current-scenario-*.json
- Latest test report and focused command under {{run.dir}}/tdd/
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}

Goal:
Prove the one new test is runnable, asserted, and fails for the intended absent or incorrect behavior.

Rules:
- Do not edit or commit files.
- Inspect the diff to confirm only one scenario became concrete and production behavior was not implemented.
- Run the exact focused command.
- Pass only when the failure meaningfully corresponds to the selected scenario.
- Fail for a passing test, missing/weak assertions, unrelated compile errors, broken fixtures, environment failures, or multiple speculative tests.

Write:
- Report: {{run.dir}}/tdd/red-report-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/tdd/red-status-{{run.round}}.json
- On failure: {{run.dir}}/tdd/red-issues-{{run.round}}.json

Status examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"meaningful red verified","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"red gate failed","issues_file":"tdd/red-issues-{{run.round}}.json"}
